net.sourceforge.waters.model.module

Interface EventListExpressionProxy

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ExpressionProxy, Proxy
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    LabelBlockProxy, PlainEventListProxy
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    EventListExpressionElement, LabelBlockElement, PlainEventListElement

    public interface EventListExpressionProxy
extends ExpressionProxy

    An expression defined by an event list.

    Event lists are used in various places in a module, where several events are grouped together. The most common application is on transitions in graphs (LabelBlockProxy), but event lists can also be used for parameter bindings (ParameterBindingProxy) of instance components or alias declarations (AliasProxy) in a module's event alias list.

    Technically, an event list is a wrapper of an object implementing the List interface, which can have two different kinds of elements.

    IdentifierProxy
    Identifiers are used to include a single event with a given name (or all elements of an array of events) in an event list. There can be simple identifiers (SimpleIdentifierProxy) that are just names or indexed identifiers (IndexedIdentifierProxy) that can have one or more array indexes.
    ForeachProxy
    This construct can be used to include several events by processing a loop.
    Author:
    Robi Malik
